    "en": {
      "title": "Nimal resigns from Ministry of Ports and Aviation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva has decided to resign from the Ministry of Ports and Aviation Services. It is also reported that the related letter has been forwarded to the President.",
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa has taken this decision as per instructions to Nimal Siripala de Silva to resign from the post of Ports and Aviation Services.",
        "According to the President's Media Division, the President has instructed the opposition leader Mr. Sajith Premadasa to temporarily step down from the ministry until an investigation is conducted into the allegations raised by the Ministry of Aviation with a private company.",
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa has ordered a formal investigation regarding this allegation, and it is reported that Mr. Nimal Siripala de Silva has decided to temporarily resign from the position of Minister of Ports, Shipping and Aviation until the investigations are completed and the relevant letter has been forwarded. will be"
      ],
